# Using Voice Gateways

<mark>The Cisco Unified Communications call-processing devices in the CUCM suite allow engineers to configure and deploy a voice system for on-network calling.</mark> On-network dialing means that the calls are contained within a private network fully controlled by a private organization. But what if you need to make a call to someone outside the local organization? This is where voice gateways come into play.<br>
<mark>__Voice gateways are responsible for the setup of off-network calling.__</mark><br>

<mark>A voice gateway is simply an IOS router that is capable of translating legacy voice communication into IP packets for transport over data networks.
